"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbc6d8cef-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbc6d8cf0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbc6d8cf1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 3102 and 3103 of this title, referred to in subsec. (a), were omitted from the Code pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5316"},"text":"section 5316 of this title","children":[],"tail":" which terminated the authority to make grants or loans under those sections after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Emergency Community Facilities Act of 1970, referred to in subsec. (a), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/431"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–431","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/886"},"text":"84 Stat. 886","children":[],"tail":", which amended sections 3102 and 3108 of this title, and enacted a provision set out as a note under this section. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3101"},"text":"section 3101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbc6d8cf2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1973—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/117/s8/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–117, § 8(a)","children":[],"tail":", provided for neighborhood facility grant authorization of $40,000,000 for fiscal year commencing "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1973","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/117/s8/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–117, § 8(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1972—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/335"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–335","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1972","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1970—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/609/s304/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–609, § 304(a)","children":[],"tail":", authorized appropriation of $50,000,000 for fiscal year commencing "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1971","children":[],"tail":", for grants under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3103"},"text":"section 3103 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/431/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–431, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", authorized appropriations for grants under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3102"},"text":"section 3102 of this title","children":[],"tail":" of not to exceed $1,000,000,000 for fiscal year commencing "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/609/s304/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–609, § 304(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1972","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1971","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/431/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–431, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1972","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1971","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1969—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/152/s305/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–152, § 305(c)","children":[],"tail":", authorized appropriations of not more than $100,000,000 for fiscal year commencing "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/152/s305/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–152, § 305(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1971","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1968—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/448/s605/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–448, § 605(b)","children":[],"tail":", authorized appropriations of not more than $350,000,000 for fiscal year commencing "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1968","children":[],"tail":", and not more than $115,000,000 for fiscal year commencing "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1969","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/448/s605/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–448, § 605(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1970","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1969","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbc6d8cf3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbc6d8cf4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Congressional Statement of Findings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/431/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–431, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/886"},"text":"84 Stat. 886","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/91/431/s2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress finds that a large number of municipalities and other entities of local government throughout the Nation are unable to finance construction of vital and urgently needed public facilities because of the shortage of funds for long-term borrowing.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress further finds that there is an immediate need for such facilities in order to provide basic safeguards for the health and well-being of the people of the United States, to check widespread pollution of irreplaceable water sources, and to provide an effective and practical method of combating rising unemployment.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbc6d8cf5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Administrative Priority for Applications Relating to Activities in Areas Affected by Base Closings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"State or unit of local government or agency thereof affected by reduction in level of expenditure or employment at Department of Defense installation located in or near such State or unit of local government, priority in processing applications for assistance under this section, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1453a"},"text":"section 1453a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
